    Additional utilities to help create Struct messages.

    Unlike com.google.protobuf.util.Structs, struct values of all supported types (numeric, string, boolean, null) and the Collections, Maps, Tables, Optionals thereof are automatically converted to their corresponding Value wrappers using ProtoValueConverter. This allows users to conveniently create Struct whose fields are often heterogeneous maps of dynamically typed values. For example: 

    
 Struct ironMan =
     struct("name", "Tony Stark", "age", 40, "talents", List.of("genius", "billionare"));

    The struct() factory methods will throw IllegalArgumentException if duplicate keys are provided. This is consistent with Map.of() and ImmutableMap.of(), and different from com.google.protobuf.util.Structs that leaves it as "undefined behavior".

    Occasionally, an application may need custom logic to convert a domain-specific type into Value, and then recursively into ListValue and/or Struct. This can be done by overriding ProtoValueConverter.convert(java.lang.Object).

    To build Struct without risk of runtime Value conversion error caused by unsupported types, use #toStruct(Function) BiCollector on a BiStream, or build it manually with StructBuilder instead.
